profileAlternative.summary:
A graduate student currently pursuing masters in Computer Engineering at San Jose State University. Highly Specialized in areas like Full-Stack Web Development, Android Development, and Networking.

Skills:
Proficient: Java, JavaScript, Android Programming, JSP, JPA, MySQL, HTML, Node JS, React JS, CSS, RESTful API, XML.
Others: AJAX, C, C++, JDBC, jQuery, JSON, Redux, Mocha, WordPress, Webpack, Heroku, Postman, Firebase, MongoDB, SQLite.
Certifications: Java 8, NodeJS, ReactJS, Spring MVC and Hibernate Frameworks.
Operating Systems and Networking Tools: Windows, Linux, Mac, Wireshark, GNS3.
Network Protocols-Labs worked: TCP/IP, HTTP, NAT, ARP, DHCP, ICMP, IGMP, UDP, BGP, SIP.

Quick learner and passionate about learning new things and technologies. Worked on many projects which helped me to be strong in programming. Good team player, I believe working in a team to solve a problem helps a lot to achieve the efficient and best solution. Good interpersonal and communication skills, working as a student and office assistant helped me to develop strong interpersonal skills.

Other activities:
Awarded with the certificate of appreciation from the city commissioner for conducting cleaning campaigns to bring awareness among the people.
Worked as Executive member of SANKYA - The mathematical forum (a technical club at Amrita).
